Danish central bank buys back CDs at 3 . 50 pct . Denmark ' s central bank said on Monday it offered to buy back 14 - day certificates of deposit ( CDs ) at a fixed yield of 3 . 50 percent plus the normal 0 . 05 percent buyback charge , unchanged from the previous two - week offer . The bank steers money market rates and liquidity through its 14 - day certificates of deposit ( CDs ) deals and state paper repos . The central bank discount and key deposit rates were unchanged at 3 . 25 percent . - - Chris Follett , Copenhagen newsroom + 45 - 33 - 969652 
